HEADWORD: Oroide
<hw>O"roide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>or</ets> gold
(L. <ets>aurum</ets>) + Gr. <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety> <def>An
alloy, chiefly of copper and zinc or tin, resembling gold in color and
brilliancy.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>oreide</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

